Source: Department of Finance
Data: Housing Information (Single detached, Single attached, … Five Plus)
https://dof.ca.gov/forecasting/demographics/estimates/e-5-population-and-housing-estimates-for-cities-counties-and-the-state-2020-2024/
Single Detached: The number of housing units that are single-family homes, typically standalone houses not attached to any other structures.
Single Attached: The number of housing units that are single-family homes, but they are attached to one or more other units (such as townhouses or duplexes).
Two to Four: The number of housing units in buildings that contain between two and four units (such as small apartment buildings or duplexes).
Five Plus: The number of housing units in buildings with five or more units (typically larger apartment buildings or complexes).

